# Final Packaging Index

## Overview
This index provides a complete, top‑level map of every asset in the release ecosystem.  
It defines where each file belongs, its purpose, and its submission destination.  
This is the final organizational layer before global distribution.

---

## 1. Manuscript & Core Files
- Final Manuscript → Kindle Direct Publishing  
- Kindle Description → Storefront Metadata  
- Release Notes → Internal Documentation  

---

## 2. Author & Press Materials
- Author Bio → Press Kit / Storefront  
- Press Summary → Press Kit  
- Media Kit Summary → Press Kit  
- Press Kit Folder → Media Distribution  

---

## 3. Storefront & Retail Assets
- Storefront Summary → Kindle Storefront  
- Storefront Tagline → Product Page Header  
- Full Storefront Pack → Retail Submission  
- Retail Metadata → KDP Metadata Fields  
- International Metadata Pack → Global Storefronts  
- Retail SEO Keywords → Search Optimization  
- Global Listing Summary → International Retail Pages  
- Global Storefront Bundle → Worldwide Distribution  

---

## 4. Promotional Materials
- One‑Line Promo → Social Media / Storefront  
- Short Promo Paragraph → Announcements / Storefront  
- Full Marketing Line → Press / Social / Retail  
- Hashtag Pack → Social Media  
- Social Release Line → Launch Week Posts  
- 30‑Day Posting Schedule → Social Media Calendar  

---

## 5. Announcement Materials
- Public Announcement → Social / Email / Website  
- Launch Week Messaging → Daily Release Posts  

---

## 6. Master Structures
- Master Release Folder → Internal Master Directory  
- Global Storefront Bundle → International Submission  
- Final Packaging Index → Master Map (this file)  

---

## Status
All components are complete, polished, and ready for final submission.  
This index marks the end of the packaging cycle and the beginning of distribution.
